The paper discusses techniques for visualizing multivariate spatial data, which involves both graphical representation and computational analysis. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including computer graphics (cs.GR), computer vision (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, since the focus of the paper is on visualization, we can assume that cs.GR is the most likely category, followed by cs.CV and cs.HC, which also deal with visual perception and interaction. The other two categories, cs.SI and cs.DS, are less directly related but may still be relevant for certain aspects of the paper, such as network analysis or data compression.
